data.name: label1.Text
data.value: Current data state is shown in table below. Final quantity of individuals requiring extra information on their weight is given in last column. Click 'Next' to proceed to add extra data.

data.name: labelLoaded.Text
data.value: Extra cards contain data on {0} taxa / species. {1} species are in common with diet.

data.name: label2.Text
data.value: Drag and drop cards in here or click button below to use additional information on individuals natural size. Use cards from similar conditions to where and when diet materials were collected.

data.name: label3.Text
data.value: Here is information from extra cards you have loaded. Turn back to load more cards or proceed to specify taxa association. Application of raw individual mass allows to recover weight of individuals anyway if any taxa is associated.

data.name: label5.Text
data.value: Here you may set association between taxa in diet and natural cards. Select row and click "Set association" to select associated species. Click "Reset" to make default association which is according full match of species name. Previously selected taxa also selected.

data.name: label4.Text
data.value: Each measured variable common for both diet and natural data is presented as column. Values in columns demontrate number (and also fraction of total unweighted count) of weight-recoverable individuals. Reorder columns to change priority of using variables.

data.name: label12.Text
data.value: You will be provided with exhausting report on how mass of exact individuals was calculated.

data.name: label8.Text
data.value: All is ready to recover weight of unweighted individuals. Also mass of species and samples will be recalculated. Press "Finish" to do this.
